commit.message: Uploading some example screenshots of the program running.

It's almost there, I can taste it. The cards look okay, the thing is
making the cards alright, I just gotta get the events to work for
clicking and changing the state to the next round of questions, whatever
the state changes to based on the data.

Making some progress. The cards look nicer, but I can't get them to
populate based on their current state. Still working on it, the error
I am getting is saying that it cannot convert undefined to an object.
I'm going to try pulling just the part I'm doing out and working on it
in a browser to see where exactly the issues lies.

Working on getting the chat cards situated appropriately. Right now
they're bunched at the top left. I am pushing to github to show my team.

Routing works!

Starting on figuring out how to do the chatbot in only a few hours!

I understand how the router works now. It's essentially a conditional
statement that places the code that matches the current route exactly
where the Route tag is. This is something I'll leave in App.js and then
have things that navigate around in other sections of the code.

Currently still trying to get the Menubar's navigation right.

Added a router, having really touched it yet. I did however flesh out
the menu a bit and got the events to work correctly after wrestling with
them for a while.

The next step is to get the routes to work with the MenuItem's. I think
that I may be having difficulty because I'm not looking to place the
navigation in the right place. Maybe I do not even need to use MenuItems
and instead need Routes. I dunno, I'm tired.

Going to add in a router and just try to get something done with it.
Creating a savepoint to go back to in case I want to try something else.
Added in James' changes to the About section.
Added the html file for the about page. Only a pararaph of text.

While I wait for more feedback regarding routing, I have hardcoded the
about section into app.js so I can start filling it out. I have put a
little boilerplate of the information that should be in there.

Fixed the menu button such that it's on the right-hand side. Also, I
did some research regarding routing. I think that the best bet would be
to use react-router-component but aviator takes a close second.

Fixed an issue with window sizing. Adding the toolbar made it such
that the window thought it was too long, added a scrollbar. May have to
do some trickery later if it tries to do something screwy when there's
actually enough content to need to scroll.
Merge branch 'master' of github.com:steveslatky/united_in_crisis_front
Update - .gitignore - .idea

Started working on the menubar after doing some research on how best
to do it. It appears that Material-ui is really nice for this sort of
thing. I had used it previously and forgot. It's in addition to and sits
on top of react to add additional functionality and makes things look
cleaner.

Now what I'll do is get it to show the menu icon on the right-hand side
as well as insert all of the links that we'll need for navigating from
the home page, the about me section, and chat.

However, now that we found a component online that may be able to
handle chat for us, we may go with that instead which would be a
floating chat box, not necessitating its own window.

Added some template files for what we're going to be
building out. This is the most basic stuff we are
going to need to have a minimally viable product.
Initializing the project with boilerplate react!
Initializing the project with boilerplate react!
Add - .editorconfig
Initial commit
